# @param {String} s1
# @param {String} s2
# @return {Boolean}
def check_strings(s1, s2)
    # Initialize hash maps to count characters at odd and even positions for both strings
    odd_counts_s1 = Hash.new(0)
    even_counts_s1 = Hash.new(0)
    odd_counts_s2 = Hash.new(0)
    even_counts_s2 = Hash.new(0)

    s1.length.times do |i|
        if i.even?
            even_counts_s1[s1[i]] += 1
            even_counts_s2[s2[i]] += 1
        else
            odd_counts_s1[s1[i]] += 1
            odd_counts_s2[s2[i]] += 1
        end
    end

    # Compare character counts at odd and even positions between s1 and s2
    odd_counts_s1 == odd_counts_s2 && even_counts_s1 == even_counts_s2
end
